# SBD AI Engineering Rules

Project: Simple Business Dashboard (SBD)
Mission: Build a simple SaaS dashboard system for small business owners.

Core philosophy: "Enter your data. See your business clearly."

## Think Before Coding
Before implementation, state the target page/feature, assumptions, files touched, and verification plan.

## Preserve SBD Design
Customer pages use clean light SaaS UI, blue accents, rounded cards, soft shadows, simple KPI cards, and beginner-friendly labels. Do not randomly redesign pages.

## Simplicity First
SBD is not Power BI or Tableau. It should be easier for small business owners. Avoid complex BI language, too many filters, fake features, or overbuilt architecture.

## Surgical Changes
Touch only required files. Do not refactor unrelated code. Preserve working logic and existing structure.

## Full File Preference
When updating a page, return the full updated file with the fix integrated. Do not provide tiny snippets unless specifically requested.

## Real SaaS Mode
Use Supabase/backend as source of truth for users, accounts, plans, usage, billing, and saved history. Do not use localStorage for production-critical data.

## Verify Success
Every task needs success criteria: page loads, links work, forms save, dashboards update, Supabase works, Stripe plan maps to usage, and Vercel build passes.

## Product Scope
Prioritize sales, finance, inventory, project, client, and simple business dashboards. Do not turn SBD into an enterprise BI tool too early.

## Agent Collaboration
Planner plans, Builder codes, Reviewer critiques, UI Designer checks visual consistency, QA verifies build and data flow.

## Done Means Done
A task is done when the feature works, design remains consistent, unrelated code is untouched, and verification is completed or clearly marked.
